  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">viṉaimuṟṟip pukunta talaimakaṉ kiḻattiyōṭuṭaṉ iruntu kūṟiyatu. <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT270-kilavi"> </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">Spoken, when he was together with HER, by HIM, who
    entered after having completed work. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT270">
          <l> tāḻiru ṭumiya miṉṉit taṇṇeṉa</l>
          <l> vīḻuṟai yiṉiya citaṟi yūḻiyiṟ</l>
          <l> kaṭippiku muraciṉ muḻaṅki yiṭittiṭittup</l>
          <l> peytiṉi vāḻiyō peruvāṉ yāmē</l>
          <l> ceyviṉai muṭitta cemma luḷḷamō</l>
          <l> ṭivaḷiṉ mēviṉa mākik kuvaḷaik</l>
          <l> kuṟuntā ṇāṇmalar nāṟu</l>
          <l> naṟumeṉ kūntaṉ mellaṇai yēmē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>May you live, great sky, now that you've rained</l>
          <l rend="indent2">under rumbling thunder <note place="foot">
              <term xml:lang="ta">muḻaṅki iṭittu iṭittu</term> : is this a synonym compound plus
    repetition, achieving an intensification?</note> like a drum beaten with the stick</l>
          <l rend="indent">for a long time pouring out coolly the descending, dripping sweet [drops]</l>
          <l rend="indent2">[and] flashing so that the hanging dark is severed.</l>
          <l rend="indent3">With an exalted mind that, since we wished for her,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">has completed the work to be done,</l>
          <l>we [are now] on a soft bed with [her of] fragrant, soft tresses <note place="foot">
              <term xml:lang="ta">kūntal mel aṇaiyēm </term> might also mean "we [are] on the soft
    bed of [her] tresses" (thus the explanation of T.V.G.).</note>
          </l>
          <l rend="indent">smelling of the short-stemmed day blossom of the waterlily.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
